0nanny.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22e8e418c9-ef1b-4da5-a522-28b54652aad3%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EIt's%20a%20challenge%3C%2Fstrong%3E%2C%3Cstrong%3E%20but%20it's%20worth%20it%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20worked%20with%20a%20lot%20of%20moms%20who%20felt%20they%20didn't%20have%20the%20time%20to%20look%20after%20themselves%20or%20that%20their%20own%20care%20was%20trivial.%20It%20was%20important%20for%20me%20to%20make%20sure%20they%20did%20things%20that%20helped%20them%20feel%20good%20about%20their%20day%2C%20such%20as%20taking%20a%20shower%2C%20getting%20out%20of%20bed%20and%20being%20able%20to%20hold%20their%20baby%2C%20or%20any%20daily%20activities%20they%20did%20before%20they%20had%20kids.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20a%20privilege%20to%20see%20babies%20learn%20to%20roll%20over%2C%20crawl%2C%20or%20walk.%20Even%20at%20night%2C%20I%20got%20to%20know%20them%20and%20their%20personalities.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20worked%20with%20one%20family%20for%20a%20year.%20They%20had%20two%20babies%2C%20and%20they%20already%20had%20two%20children.%20Both%20of%20the%20parents%20sometimes%20worked%20night%20shifts.%20Both%20of%20the%20babies%20would%20vomit%20up%20their%20milk%20and%20cry%20through%20the%20night.%20Some%20of%20those%20nights%20were%20very%20long.%20Their%20mom%20would%20want%20to%20help%20out%2C%20and%20I'd%20have%20to%20encourage%20her%20to%20take%20a%20nap.%20She'd%20have%20to%20get%20up%20at%205%20a.m.%20to%20get%20her%20other%20kids%20ready%20for%20school.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20we%20got%20the%20babies%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhen-to-start-sleep-training-your-newborn%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esleep-trained%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20their%20mom%20was%20so%20excited%20that%20she%20could%20get%20a%20couple%20of%20hours%20of%20sleep.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20hard%20but%20rewarding.%20I%20decided%20to%20take%20a%20break%20this%20year.%20Now%2C%20I%20take%20on%20clients%20on%20a%20case-by-case%20basis.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20dat