20just%20once%20in%20500%20to%201%2C000%20years.%20Damages%20could%20top%20%241%20billion.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20new%20era%20of%20extreme%20rain%20prompted%20the%20US%20National%20Academy%20of%20Sciences%20on%20Tuesday%20to%20recommend%20a%20major%20reboot%20of%20the%20country's%20%26quot%3Bprobable%20maximum%20precipitation%26quot%3B%20estimates%2C%20which%20guide%20infrastructure%20development.%20They%20haven't%20been%20updated%20since%201999%20nationally%2C%20and%20in%20some%20cases%20not%20for%2060%20years.%20More%20than%2016%2C000%20at-risk%20dams%20and%2050%20nuclear%20power%20plants%2C%20all%20of%20them%20aging%2C%20face%20new%20extremes.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20report%20lays%20out%20ways%20to%20use%20modern%20climate%20models%20to%20update%20the%20analysis%20to%20account%20for%20global%20warming.%20It's%20an%20acknowledgment%20that%20%26quot%3Bsuper-wild%20weather%26quot%3B%20is%20entering%20a%20new%20phase%20and%20the%20US%20has%20to%20be%20prepared%2C%20says%20John%20Nielsen-Gammon%2C%20a%20professor%20at%20Texas%20A%26amp%3BM%20University%20and%20the%20state's%20climatologist%2C%20who%20co-authored%20the%20study.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20weather%20is%20no%20longer%20an%20even%20roll%20of%20the%20dice.%20It's%20more%20like%20throwing%20loaded%20dice%20that%20have%20sixes%20on%20three%20sides%20-%20or%20sevens%20and%20eights%2C%20says%20Katharine%20Hayhoe%2C%20a%20distinguished%20professor%20at%20Texas%20Tech%20University%20who%20studies%20climate%20impacts.%20The%20term%20%26quot%3Bglobal%20warming%26quot%3B%20itself%20suggests%20a%20kind%20of%20predictability%20that%20may%20no%20longer%20suit%20the%20times.%20%26quot%3BThese%20days%20I%20think%20it's%20much%20more%20appropriate%20to%20call%20it%20'global%20weirding%2C'%26quot%3B%20Hayhoe%20says.%20%26quot%3BWherever%20we%20live%2C%20our%20weather%20is%20getting%20much%20weirder.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGreenhouse%20gas%20pollution%20made%20last%20year%201.3C%20hotter%20than%20before%20the%20Industrial%20Revolution.%20This%20past%20May%20marked%20the%2012th-consecutive%20month%20of%20record-breaking%20average%20temperatures%20for%20the%20planet%2C%20and%20the%20oceans%20have%20registered%20new%20levels%20of%20heat%20every%20day%20for%20over%20a%20year.%20That's%20caused%20freak%20rain%20and%20hail%2C%20more%20destructive%20storms%20and%20even%20unexpected%20cold%20snaps%20-%20London%2C%20Paris%20and%20Berlin%20and%20other%20parts%20of%20Europe%20saw%20temperatures%20earlier%20in%20June%20drop%20below%20levels%20from%20last%20Christmas%20Eve.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20it's%20the%20heat%20and%20associated%20droughts%2C%20floods%20and%20wildfires%20that%20have%20become%20the%20more%20prolific%20indicator%20of%20today's%20weird%2C%20wild%20weather.%20The%20threat%20of%20infernos%20is%20at%20extreme%20levels%20in%20Greece%20and%20Spain%2C%20with%20risks%20spreading%20to%20the%20French%20Riviera.%20Thermometers%20in%20Egypt%20flirted%20with%20a%20record-high%2051C%20(124F)%20earlier%20this%20month.%20Floods%20have%20damaged%20infrastructure%20and%20threatened%20crops%20in%20China%2C%20while%20much%20of%20South%20Asia%20has%20faced%20temperatures%20that%20tested%20the%20limits%20of%20the%20human%20body.%20Extreme%20heat%20in%20Gaza%20worsened%20the%20humanitarian%20crisis.%20A%20deluge%20of%20rain%20after%20years%20of%20drought%20in%20East%20Africa%20claimed%20hundreds%20of%20lives%20and%20swept%20away%20livestock.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EErich%20Fischer%2C%20a%20climate%20scientist%20at%20ETH%20Zurich%2C%20has%20been%20trying%20to%20do%20for%20heat%20something%20similar%20to%20what%20US%20researchers%20want%20to%20do%20for%20precipitation.%20His%20work%20in%20recent%20years%20has%20helped%20demonstrate%20that%20temperature%20records%20around%20the%20world%20are%20falling%20by%20greater%20and%20greater%20margins%2C%20meaning%20there's%20%26quot%3Bincreasing%20probability%20of%20record-shattering%20climate%20extremes%2C%26quot%3B%20as%20he%20wrote%20with%20co-authors%20in%20a%202021%20paper.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFischer's%20research%20essentially%20predicted%20the%20extremely%20rare%202021%20heat%20wave%20that%20hit%20western%20North%20America%2C%20when%20the%20region%20experienced%20its%20hottest%20June%20on%20record%20and%201%2C400%20people%20died.%20A%20study%20Fischer%20led%20last%20year%20identified%20places%20that%20might%20have%20undetected%20potential%20for%20heat%20waves%20of%20that%20magnitude.%20His%20danger%20list%20included%20Paris%2C%20which%20will%20host%20more%20than%201%20million%20visitors%20for%20the%20Summer%20Olympic%20Games.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BNow%20that%20we%20know%20that%20these%20events%20become%20more%20frequent%2C%20we%20should%20expect%20to%20see%20more%20of%20these%20jumps%2C%26quot%3B%20Fisher%20says.%20With%20the%20realization%20that%20impossible%20weather%20was%20now%20in%20many%20ways%20possible%2C%20he%20says%20he's%20been%20investigating%20the%20next%20logical%20question%3A%20%26quot%3BWhat%20is%20really%20the%20biggest%20event%20that%20people%20need%20to%20prepare%20for%3F%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBased%20on%20the%20first%20five%20months%20of%202024%2C%20it's%20become%20certain%20this%20year%20will%20end%20as%20one%20of%20the%20five%20warmest%20on%20record.%20There's%20now%20a%20more%20than%2060%25%20chance%20that%20it%20will%20overtake%202023%20to%20top%20the%20list.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPart%20of%20what%20drove%20temperatures%20higher%20through%20the%20first%20half%20of%202024%2C%20and%20helped%20boost%20extremes%2C%20was%20the%20fading%20El%20Nino%2C%20a%20heating%20of%20the%20equatorial%20Pacific%20that%20warms%20the%20globe.%20Additional%20heat%20has%20come%20from%20a%20counterintuitive%20change%3A%20Regulations%20meant%20to%20clean%20up%20pollution%20from%20shipping%20began%20to%20reduce%20the%20emission%20of%20sulfur%20which%20-%20though%20harmful%20to%20health%20-%20can%20also%20help%20cool%20the%20atmosphere%20by%20blocking%20sunlight.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EScientists%20warn%20that%20the%20danger%20ahead%20isn't%20just%20from%20supercharged%20weather%20catastrophes.%20A%20warmer%20planet%20increases%20the%20chances%20of%20%26quot%3Bcompound%20events%2C%26quot%3B%20where%20multiple%20disasters%20-%20natural%20and%20manmade%20-%20occur%20at%20the%20same%20time%20or%20place%2C%20exacerbating%20their%20combined%20impact.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20prime%20example%20can%20be%20found%20in%20Texas%2C%20where%20high%20temperatures%20contributed%20to%20the%20state's%20largest-ever%20wildfire.%20Abnormally%20dry%20conditions%20in%20the%20Canadian%20province%20of%20Alberta%20translated%20into%20an%20early%20start%20to%20fire%20season.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20other%20cases%2C%20impacts%20spread%20across%20borders.%20In%20March%2C%20Saharan%20dust%20storms%20blew%20north%2C%20turning%20skies%20yellow%20and%20orange%20in%20Sicily%20and%20degrading%20air%20quality%20from%20Greece%2C%20through%20Italy%2C%20to%20France%2C%20which%20also%20saw%20intense%20rain.%20Spiking%20food%20and%20energy%20prices%20have%20also%20overlapped%20with%20harsh%20weather%20conditions%2C%20for%20example%2C%20magnifying%20the%20consequences%20of%20the%20yearslong%20drought%20in%20Syria%2C%20Iraq%20and%20Iran.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20common%20denominator%20here%20is%20rising%20temperatures%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Amir%20AghaKouchak%2C%20a%20professor%20at%20University%20of%20California%20at%20Irvine%20who%20has%20studied%20the%20future%20risk%20of%20compound%20events.%20%26quot%3BTemperature%20has%20increased%20significantly%2C%20and%20it's%20contributing%20to%20all%20of%20%5Bthe%20disasters%5D%20and%20it's%20intensifying%20maybe%20the%20relationship%20between%20different%20hazards.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESome%20areas%20have%20also%20had%20to%20deal%20with%20different%20extremes%20in%20quick%20succession.%20The%20Philippines%20shut%20down%20schools%20and%20power%20plants%20in%20April%20as%20temperatures%20soared.%20Now%20the%20government%20has%20warned%20increased%20rainfall%20could%20hurt%20the%20country's%20food%20supply%20as%20El%20Nino%20ends%20and%20cooler%20conditions%20take%20hold.%20Forest%20fires%20in%20February%20killed%20more%20than%20100%20people%20in%20Chile%2C%20where%20historic%20downpours%20are%20currently%20causing%20chaos%20in%20the%20region's%20typically%20dry%20climate.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EExtreme%20weather%20can%20become%20novel%20just%20by%20lasting%20for%20previously%20unexpected%20lengths%20of%20time.%20In%20Southeast%20Asia%2C%20for%20example%2C%20climate%20change%20now%20means%20heat%20waves%20can%20last%20for%20months.%20Prolonged%20flooding%20left%20more%20than%20500%20dead%20in%20Kenya%2C%20Tanzania%2C%20Uganda%20and%20Burundi.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERenzo%20Guinto%2C%20an%20associate%20professor%20of%20planetary%20health%20at%20the%20Duke-NUS%20Medical%20School%20in%20Singapore%2C%20worries%20that%20affected%20nations%20are%20mostly%20focused%20on%20responding%20to%20immediate%20health%20dangers%20and%20risk%20ignoring%20underlying%20causes.%20%26quot%3BWhat%20we%20now%20need%2C%20in%20an%20era%20of%20multiple%20extreme%20weather%20phenomena%2C%20is%20to%20be%20less%20reactive%20and%20more%20anticipatory%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20says.%20%26quot%3BWe%20are%20just%20perpetuating%20a%20vicious%20cycle%20of%20emissions%20and%20extreme%20events%2C%20and%20the%20ultimate%20victims%20of%20this%20cycle%20are%20human%20beings.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20year's%20weird%20weather%20has%20affected%20every%20corner%20of%20the%20global%20economy%2C%20from%20power%20grids%20to%20air%20travel.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20study%20published%20in%20Nature%20in%20April%20projected%20climate%20damages%20could%20cost%20the%20global%20economy%20%2438%20trillion%20(in%202005%20dollars)%20per%20year%20by%202049%2C%20overshadowing%20the%20estimated%20%246%20trillion%20needed%20to%20cut%20planet-warming%20emissions%20in%20line%20with%20the%20goals%20of%20the%20Paris%20Agreement.%20Spending%20on%20clean%20technologies%20hit%20a%20record%20%241.8%20trillion%20in%202023%2C%20according%20to%20BloombergNEF%2C%20still%20far%20short%20of%20what's%20needed.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECattle%20graze%20on%20an%20island%20of%20unburnt%20grass%20in%20the%20aftermath%20of%20the%20Smokehouse%20Creek%20fire%20near%20Pampa%2C%20Texas%2C%20in%20March.%20Photographer%3A%20Scott%20Olson%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20doesn't%20help%20that%20some%20of%20the%20world's%20most-ambitious%20climate%20policies%20are%20under%20attack%20in%20Europe%20and%20the%20US%20as%20voters%20push%20back%20on%20gas%20stove%20phase-outs%20and%20sustainable%20farming%20measures.%20Emerging%20markets%2C%20which%20will%20need%20to%20make%20the%20biggest%20leap%20to%20clean%20energies%2C%20are%20struggling%20to%20win%20a%20bigger%20share%20of%20global%20green%20investments.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EStill%2C%20it's%20not%20enough%20to%20just%20focus%20on%20cutting%20emissions%2C%20says%20Rohit%20Magotra%2C%20deputy%20director%20at%20Integrated%20Research%20and%20Action%20for%20Development%2C%20a%20climate%20consultancy%20and%20research%20firm%20based%20in%20New%20Delhi.%20Rapid%20urbanization%20means%20these%20weather%20disasters%20are%20increasingly%20devastating%2C%20and%20cities%20in%20developing%20nations%20need%20to%20build%20early%20warning%20systems%20and%20climate-proof%20infrastructure%20so%20they%20can%20be%20more%20resilient.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BExtreme%20weather%20events%20are%20getting%20more%20intense%20and%20more%20frequent.%20The%20geographies%20that%20they%20impact%20are%20also%20widening%2C%20hitting%20some%20of%20the%20most%20vulnerable%20people%20in%20the%20world%2C%26quot%3B%20Magotra%20says.%20%26quot%3BAdaptation%20is%20as%20critical%20as%20mitigation.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1718778360000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-06%2F2bo340h8_heatwave-reuters-_625x300_19_June_24.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fdeadly-de